Source 2 International (1980-1984), was an exchange service that utilized database systems to match buyers and sellers of electrical components, much as the stock exchange matches buyers and sellers of securities. It was a sales channel for equipment makers with unwieldy inventories and a new source of components for manufacturers with parts shortages. Developed and run in Santa Clara California. The exchange used the power of computer systems to match buyers and sellers of components, much as the stock exchange matches buyers and sellers of securities. It was once a sales channel for equipment makers with unwieldy inventories and a new source of components for manufacturers with parts shortages.
